            - **Precambrian to Cambrian Transition**: The Cambrian explosion marks the appearance of most major animal phyla.
            - **Mesozoic Era**: Known as the age of reptiles, especially dinosaurs.
            - **Cenozoic Era**: Known as the age of mammals, following the extinction of the dinosaurs.""",
