            "summary": "The movement of continents explains the distribution of species.",
            "details": """The theory of continental drift helps explain how similar species can be found on continents that are now far apart.
            - **Gondwana**: Ancient supercontinent whose breakup explains the distribution of similar species in South America, Africa, India, and Australia.
            - **Marsupials**: Found in Australia and South America, their distribution is explained by the movement of continents.
            - **Fossil Distribution**: Similar fossils found on different continents support the idea that the continents were once connected.""",
            "sources": ["https://www.nationalgeographic.org/encyclopedia/continental-drift/", "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1342937X22000444"]
